rgraduate, master’s, PhD, language courses, etc.).\n\n### 2. Check Admission Requirements\n- Each university will have specific admission criteria.\n- Typical requirements include academic transcripts, language proficiency (HSK for Chinese programs or IELTS/TOEFL for English programs), letters of recommendation, a personal statement, etc.\n\n### 3. Apply for Admission\n- Apply directly through the university’s admissions portal or via Chinese government scholarship platforms if applying for scholarships.\n- Submit necessary documents, application forms, and pay application fees.\n\n### 4. Receive Admission Notice\n- Once admitted, you will receive an official Admission Notice (录取通知书) from the university.\n\n### 5. Apply for a Student Visa (X Visa)\nTo study in China, you will need an X visa:\n\n#### Documents required for X visa application:\n- Valid passport (with at least 6 months validity and blank pages).\n- Completed visa application form.\n- Recent passport-sized photos.\n- Admission Notice from the Chinese university.\n- JW202 or JW201 Form (Visa Application for Study in China), issued by the university.\n- Proof of financial means (in some cases).\n- Medical examination report (may be required depending on your home country and university).\n\n### 6. Visa Application\n- Apply at the Chinese embassy or consulate in your country.\n- Some countries may allow online or through visa application centers.\n\n### 7. Arrival & Residence Permit\n- After entering China with the X visa (typically valid for 30 days), apply for a Residence Permit at the local Public Security Bureau within 30 days.\n- The Residence Permit allows you to stay in China for the duration of your study.\n\n---\n\nIf you want, I can assist you further with details based on your nationality, preferred university, or program. Just let me know!',NULL,NULL,NULL,'read',0,0,NULL,'2026-03-07 05:09:30','2026-03-07 05:09:36','\"{\\\"confidence\\\":0.5,\\\"source\\\":\\\"ai\\\"}\"','wamid.HBgMMjU0NzExODA3N